  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="9">EDP Sciences</subfield>
    <subfield code="a">The Pierre Auger Observatory studies the most energetic cosmic rays arriving at Earth, those with energies from 10^17 eV up to 10^20 eV and beyond. In continuous operation since 2004, the Observatory employs two complementary detection techniques for measuring air showers induced by those extremely energetic particles. For the past few years new detectors and techniques are being added in order to augment the sensitivity of the measurements. Data accumulated in ten years have led to major advances in our knowledge of the origin and nature of cosmic rays. We present a summary of the latest results for the spectrum of cosmic rays, their arrival directions and composition, as well as the challenges for the future operation of the Observatory.</subfield>
  </datafield>
